headline: VQ Capital Launches an AI-Driven Platform Engineered for the Next Generation of Investments
summary: VQ Capital launched today as a thesis-driven, AI-native investment platform designed to scale companies into category leaders. The firm focuses on two foundational theses: the AI Transformation of Consumer Companies and the "Golden Dome" for Cyber Intelligence.

headline: Assessing Expedia After Its 2025 Surge And Strengthening Travel Recovery Narrative
summary: Wondering if Expedia Group is still a smart buy after its run up, or if the easy money has already been made? Let us unpack whether the current share price lines up with the underlying value. Expedia has quietly kept climbing, with the stock up 2.1% over the last week, 2.4% over the past month, and 42.7% year to date, adding to a 40.6% gain over 1 year and 178.8% over 3 years. headline: Moat Stocks Gain On Health Care Strength, Tech Slowdown
summary:
Moat Index gained 1.53% in November, supported by health care and broader market participation.
Merck and Amgen were top Moat Index contributors, benefiting from strong demand and pipelines.
